  <md:title>Why Do Property Rights Exist?</md:title>
  <md:abstract>Why do property rights appear in some societies and not in others? Why do property rights exist in the first place? In this video, Professor Dan Russell of the University of Arizona discusses Harold Demsetz’s essay “Toward a Theory of Property Rights” and explains that property rights emerge in response to a problem, but not when the cost of enforcing property rights would be greater than solving the problem is worth.</md:abstract>
